Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG -The bodies of seven workers have been discovered at Lismor farm, outside Kestell in the Free State. It's alleged, that the farm owner found the bodies of six women and a man in their house on the farm on Friday. Police say the victims were shot by unknown suspects and the motive is not yet known. Free State Police Commissioner Baile Motswenyane has urgently mobilised officers to find the perpetrators. 